Preheat oven to 375 degrees.  In a #large bowl{}, mix @condensed cream of celery soup{2%cans} (two 10 3/4 oz cans), @sour cream{2%cups}, @water{1/2%cup}, and @pepper{1/2%tsp} until blended.  Stir in @frozen O'Brien potatoes{2%packages} (2 packages, 28 oz. each), @cubed Velveeta{1%package} (one 16 oz. package), and @cubed fully cooked ham{2.5%cups}.
Transfer to #two greased 2-qt. baking dishes{}.  Bake, covered, 40 minutes.  Uncover; bake 10-15 minutes longer or until bubbly.  Let stand 10 minutes before serving.  Freeze option: Cover and freeze unbaked casseroles.  To use, partially thaw in refrigerator overnight.  Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before baking.  Preheat oven to 375 degrees.  Bake casseroles as directed, increasing time as necessary to heat through and for a thermometer inserted in center to read 165 degrees.